HEADWORD: Schizont
<hw>Schi"zont</hw> <pr>(sk⟦imac⟧"z⟦ocr⟧nt <it>or</it>
sk⟦imac⟧z"⟦ocr⟧nt)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/, <?/, p.pr.,
cleaving.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>In certain Sporozoa, a cell
formed by the growth of a sporozoite or merozoite (in a cell or
corpuscle of the host) which segment by superficial cleavage, without
encystment or conjugation, into merozoites.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

